text: The 2019–20 Y-League season (also known as the 2019–20 Foxtel Y-League season for sponsorship reasons) is the twelfth season of the Australian Y-League, the premier national competition for youth football in the country. ==Teams== Ten teams is competing in the league – the same ten from the previous season (divided into two groups). It is scheduled to run from 16 November 2019, through to the Grand Final on 1/2 February 2020. ===Conference A=== Conference A contains teams from outside of New South Wales and the Australian Capital Territory. {| class="wikitable sortable" |- !
